                                                                                                                       7                                      Young for Team India 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) has appointed Australian Michael Young as the fielding consultant of the Indian team.         
	He will be joining the team on Sunday and will be with Mahendra Singh Dhonis men till the end of the one-day International (ODI) series against Sri Lanka, according to a BCCI release Friday.         
	That implies he will also be helping Team India during their two Twenty20 Internationals against Sri Lanka which precedes the ODI series.         
	Chicago-born Young, a former minor league baseball player in America, was approached by Cricket Australia in 2000 and was with the Australian team as an assistant coach till 2005.         
	India had sacked their full time fielding coach Robin Singh, as well as their bowling coach Venkatesh Prasad, just before the seven-match ODI series against Australia at home.         
	Young also coached the Australian baseball team at the Seoul Olympics in 1988.                                                                                                                     
